HEADWORD: Xystus
<hw>Xys"tus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>xystus</ets>, Gr. <?/, from <?/ to
scrape, polish; -- so called from its smooth and polished floor.]</ety>
<fld>(Anc. Arch.)</fld> <def>A long and open portico, for athletic
